<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4770248>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Fig. 4. Sinetectula farinosa (Gould, 1850) gen. et comb. nov. A–D. Specimen from the Marshall Islands, Kwajalein Atoll, in cave at Oceanside of West reef, depth 12 m, 14.6 mm long (KF 4766). E–G. Specimen with same collection data as for preceding, 15.6 mm long (KF 4766). H–I. Specimen from Mozambique, Fernao Velosa Bay, depth 3–4 m, 18.6 mm long (KF 5378). Scale bar: 2.0 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4770248/files/figure.png" .

